item.description:
@JUMPHIM wrote:

[quote author=roflcopterofl link=topic=494624.msg3617583#msg3617583 date=1307121726]I highly doubt the second you picked up a rscd source you new exactly what is going on

No one could pick up a source code of that size and know instantly ‘what is going on’ as there’s not just one way to program. Like everyone else I have to study the code and figure things out as I go along.

(maybe not even today judging by the topics you are posting(no offence :D)).

No I don’t fully understand every single part of the source code. Far from it and I’ve never said otherwise. There’s very, very few people on here who can safely say that they do. The client has some baffling code in it which takes a lot of time to understand. Admittedly it’s made a lot harder by the obfuscation and lack of comments though. What’s your point?

I’d also like to say that Asylum and I were humiliating you so much you removed most of your posts in this topic:

I deleted every post I could throughout the entire forum, it was not specific to that thread and nothing to do with the apparent ‘humiliation’

a) Pocket cash from RSCE

The money generated monthly sits in a bank account. A direct debit is taken monthly to pay the outgoings. Sometimes there is more money in the bank account than is required to pay the outgoings. What should happen to it?

If I spend the money paying developers to improve the game it results in spastics like you running around Mopar saying I have to pay everyone to do stuff for me because I’m incapable. If you look through your old posts you will see that you have done this several times.

If I just leave the money sitting there you accuse me of ‘pocketing cash’. If you look through your old posts you will see that you have done this several times.

Need to stop pretending that you know java (not implying that I know it)

Who can say that they do know Java then? You have never seen me code, you have no idea how much knowledge of Java programming I have.

It seems very odd that these questions of yours are surfacing after Zilent left

What questions? I asked for Project P2P’s source code. No questions were asked…[/quote]
dude dont even xplain screw them pricks make your money for your bitches you earned it no matter how you did it
